**Online Learning Platform**
Welcome to the MindSpark!
This platform aims to provide a seamless and interactive learning experience for students, teachers, and institutions.
It offers a variety of features such as course creation, enrollment, progress tracking, and interactive discussions to make learning both effective and engaging.

**Features**

**Course Creation:**
Teachers can easily create, update, and manage courses, including multimedia content such as videos, quizzes, and assignments.
**User Accounts:**
Different user roles are supported, including students, instructors, and administrators.
**Course Enrollment:** 
Students can browse and enroll in courses based on their interests or academic requirements.
**Progress Tracking:**
Students can monitor their progress through courses with milestones, grades, and completion certificates.
**Interactive Discussions:**
Built-in forums and chatrooms for students to discuss course material and collaborate.
**Quizzes and Assessments:**
Teachers can create quizzes and assignments to evaluate student performance.
**Multimedia Support:**
Courses can include videos, slides, readings, and interactive simulations.
**Responsive Design:**
The platform is designed to be fully responsive, working on desktops, tablets, and mobile devices.
**Technologies Used**
**Frontend:** React.js, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, JavaScript
**Backend:** Node.js, Express
**Database:** MongoDB, Mongoose
**Authentication:** JWT (JSON Web Token)
**Hosting:** AWS, Heroku
**Other Tools:** WebSockets for real-time communication, Redux for state management
**Usage**
**For Students:**
Create an account or log in.
Browse courses and enroll in the ones you are interested in.
Track your progress, complete quizzes, and interact with fellow learners and instructors.
**For Instructors:**
Create and manage your own courses.
Set quizzes, assignments, and monitor students' progress.
For Admins:
Manage user accounts, roles, and monitor activity across the platform.
